msgid "Stone Age"
msgstr "Stone Age"

#: ../../S/Stone-Age.rst:7
msgid "n\\.,adj\\."
msgstr "名詞・形容詞"

#: ../../S/Stone-Age.rst:10
msgid ""
"In computer folklore, an ill-defined period from ENIAC (ca. 1943) to the "
"mid-1950s; the great age of electromechanical :ref:`dinosaur`\\s. Sometimes "
"used for the entire period up to 1960--61 (see :ref:`Iron-Age`\\); however, "
"it is funnier and more descriptive to characterize the latter period in "
"terms of a ‘Bronze Age’ era of transistor-logic, pre-ferrite- :ref:`core` "
"machines with drum or CRT mass storage (as opposed to just mercury delay "
"lines and/or relays). See also :ref:`Iron-Age`\\."
msgstr ""
"コンピュータの民間伝承において、ENIAC(およそ1943年)から1950年代半ばまでの、漠然と定められた時期。電気機械式の\\ "
":ref:`dinosaur`\\ たちの偉大な時代。時には1960〜61年までの全期間を指すのにも使われる(\\ :ref:`Iron-Age`\\ "
"を参照)。とはいえ、後者の時期を、(単なる水銀遅延線やリレーではなく)ドラムやCRTの大容量記憶を備えたトランジスタ論理・フェライト\\ "
":ref:`core`\\ 以前の機械からなる‘青銅器時代’として特徴づけるほうが、おかしくもありより的確である。\\ :ref:`Iron-"
"Age`\\ も参照。"

#: ../../S/Stone-Age.rst:19
msgid "How things weren't in the  :ref:`Stone-Age`\\."
msgstr ":ref:`Stone-Age`\\ には物事はそうではなかった様子。"

